---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cameroon Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/cameroon/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Ghana for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/ghana' },
  { title: 'Kenya for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kenya' },
  { title: 'Senegal for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/senegal' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'cameroonFit', header: 'Cameroon Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XAF$295,000-421,500/mo', cameroonFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XAF$345,000-493,000/mo', cameroonFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XAF$265,500-379,350/mo', cameroonFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XAF$246,750-352,500/mo', cameroonFit: 'Very Good' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'XAF$265,500-421,500', annual: 'XAF$3.19M-5.06M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'XAF$364,200-562,000', annual: 'XAF$4.37M-6.74M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'XAF$489,500-754,350', annual: 'XAF$5.87M-9.05M' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'XAF$15,000-50,000/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Evacuation to Paris', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'XAF$15M-45M' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Cameroon 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Cameroon. Africa in miniature, bilingual culture, limited healthcare, and coverage for visitors 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Cameroon"
  subheadline="Cameroon offers 'Africa in miniature' with diverse landscapes, bilingual French/English culture, wildlife, and beaches—primarily for those with family connections or professional reasons, with security concerns in some regions."
  heroImage="/images/countries/cameroon-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Cameroon</h2>
  <p>
    Cameroon is called "Africa in miniature" for its diverse geography—beaches, rainforest, savanna, mountains, and desert. Bilingual (French and English) former colonial heritage. Primarily chosen by those with Cameroonian family connections or professional ties. Security concerns in some regions limit typical tourism retirement.
  </p>

  <p>
    Yaoundé is capital with embassies. Douala is economic center with best healthcare. Kribi offers beaches. Mount Cameroon area offers trekking. Population ~27 million. Paris (6 hours) provides medical backup for complex cases.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Security Considerations</h3>
    <ul class="text-amber-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Anglophone regions:</strong> Ongoing conflict; avoid Northwest/Southwest</li>
      <li><strong>Far North:</strong> Boko Haram presence; avoid</li>
      <li><strong>Urban crime:</strong> Petty crime in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Safer areas:</strong> Douala, Yaoundé, Kribi generally safe</li>
      <li><strong>Target:</strong> Those with family ties and local knowledge</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Cameroon Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Cameroon healthcare is limited—Clinique de l'Aéroport and La Cathédrale (Douala) are better private options. Yaoundé has some facilities. Public healthcare underfunded. Complex cases typically evacuate to Paris with strong French healthcare connections. Limited specialists locally.
  </p>

  <p>
    Paris is primary evacuation destination—Air France connections, French language, and excellent hospitals. International insurance with French coverage essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">French Healthcare Connection</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      French colonial ties mean Paris is natural evacuation destination—6-hour flight, same language, excellent hospitals. Wealthy Cameroonians regularly travel to France for medical care. Include France/Europe in insurance coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Cameroon visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Required for most nationalities. Apply through embassy. 90-day maximum.
  </p>

  <h3>Business Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For business activities. Various categories.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For long-term stays. Various categories through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Dual Nationality</h3>
  <p>
    Cameroon accepts dual citizenship. Diaspora returnees may have existing Cameroonian citizenship.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Cameroon:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Extended stay:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> France/Europe coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Security:</strong> Avoid conflict zones</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Cameroon</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance with France evacuation coverage essential. Local private clinics in Douala handle routine care. Paris provides complex care backup. Include security evacuation consideration.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Cameroon, French evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Cameroon</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong global network, France access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Paris access:</strong> Primary evacuation destination</li>
    <li><strong>French coverage:</strong> Natural healthcare connection</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Cameroon with France evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Cameroon (XAF ~655 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Douala base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Paris network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Affordable locally:</strong> Low daily costs</li>
    <li><strong>Avoid conflict zones:</strong> Safety first</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: French-Cameroonian Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,500/month pension. Family in Douala. Dual citizenship.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with France and Cameroon coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XAF$310,000/month (~$475). Family connection; Paris backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Development Professional, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month. Former NGO. Yaoundé based.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with evacuation focus.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XAF$360,000/month (~$550). Professional connection; comprehensive.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Anglophone Diaspora</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Family in Southwest region (conflict area).</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Currently NOT advisable. Wait for stability.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Alternative:</strong> Consider meeting family in Douala or abroad until situation improves.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Cameroon safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Variable—Douala and Yaoundé relatively safe with precautions. Anglophone regions (Northwest, Southwest) have ongoing conflict. Far North has Boko Haram presence. Check current advisories. Major cities manageable with local knowledge.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need French?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful—Cameroon is officially bilingual but French dominates in most areas. English common in (currently problematic) Anglophone regions. French helps everywhere. Healthcare often in French.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is "Africa in miniature"?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Geographic diversity—beaches, rainforest, savanna, mountains, desert all in one country. Over 250 ethnic groups. Rich biodiversity. Culturally diverse. Can experience many African landscapes in one nation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why choose Cameroon over Ghana?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Family ties typically—most Westerners in Cameroon have family or professional connections. Ghana is safer, more tourist-friendly, English-speaking. Cameroon for those with specific Cameroonian connections; Ghana for general African experience.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Consider Safer Alternatives</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Similar African experience with better safety.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/insurance-for/seniors/in/ghana" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Ghana Guide</a>
      <a href="/insurance-for/seniors/in/senegal" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Senegal Guide</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Parts of Cameroon have serious security concerns. Avoid Anglophone regions (Northwest, Southwest) and Far North. This guide is for informational purposes only. Always check current travel advisories before travel.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
